  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/dr-cou1-noncannulated-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework achieves the required credibility level for 12 of 13 V&V 40 factors. The single deficiency in Test conditions (achieved 2, required 3) is accepted on the basis of regulatory precedent: ASTM F1717 static compression-bending is the standard submission test for pedicle screw constructs and is sufficient for the stated COU. All three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (percent difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). The model is accepted as credible for predicting non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending performance in the regulatory submission context. Aleatory uncertainty arising from specimen-to-specimen variability and material batch effects is discussed qualitatively in the validation report; formal UQ artifacts are linked to two of three validation results.",
